## Component Comparison

### Before
```tsx
// Complex, repetitive markup
<div>
  <label htmlFor="field" className={labelClasses}>
    Label
    <span className="text-red-500 ml-1">*</span>
  </label>
  <input
    type="text"
    id="field"
    value={field}
    onChange={(e) => setField(e.target.value)}
    className={`${inputClasses} ${errors.field ? 'border-red-500' : ''}`}
  />
  {errors.field && (
    <p className="text-red-600 text-sm mt-1">{errors.field}</p>
  )}
</div>
```

### After
```tsx
// Clean, DRY, consistent
<FormGroup label="Label" required error={errors.field}>
  <EnhancedInput
    value={field}
    onChange={(e) => setField(e.target.value)}
    invalid={!!errors.field}
  />
</FormGroup>
```

**Benefits:**
- 50% less code
- Automatic error handling
- Consistent styling
- Better accessibility

